bioLine3: Anyone can dress up, dress down and re-stitch the pixels of the visual dataset.
bioLine4: Hide? Opt out of the great game?
bioLine5: Let bot farms keep pumping out stock-milled waifu templates and flat, same-tone masks on loop?
bioPara1: Run louder machines. Run better stacks. Run more ethereal aesthetics. New cities every frame. With the closet of a rotating cast of indie designers pushing looks straight into your runtime.
bioPara2: At that scale, imitation loses economic meaning, replaced by systems that run identities across every surface at the same time. Inside open systems, you and your models multiply across the network in mirrored executions, and the incentive to take you instead of become you collapses under its own weight.
